Nowadays, more and more people want to get things done instantly (services, information, tasks). Why is this? Do you think this is a positive or negative development?

The growing tendency for people to expect immediate results in services, information access, and everyday tasks has become increasingly evident in modern society. This shift is primarily driven by technological advancements and fast-paced lifestyles, and in my view, it is largely a negative development.

One of the main factors behind this trend is the widespread availability of digital technology. With high-speed internet and advanced mobile applications, people can now access information or complete tasks within seconds. As a result, they have become accustomed to this level of convenience and begin to expect instant responses in almost every aspect of life. In addition, modern lifestyles are often characterized by heavy workloads and time pressure, which leads individuals to prioritize speed and efficiency. For example, the popularity of food delivery and online banking services clearly reflects people’s preference for quick and convenient solutions.

However, this growing reliance on immediacy has several negative consequences. Firstly, it undermines important qualities such as patience and perseverance. When individuals become used to instant gratification, they are less willing to engage in activities that require sustained effort, such as academic study or long-term career development. For instance, students who depend heavily on AI tools for quick answers may struggle to develop independent thinking and problem-solving skills.

Secondly, the emphasis on speed often comes at the expense of quality. When tasks are completed too quickly, there is less time for careful consideration, which can lead to mistakes and poor decision-making. Over time, this habit of prioritizing speed over depth may result in more superficial outcomes in both personal and professional contexts.

In conclusion, although the demand for instant results is a natural outcome of technological progress and modern living, it ultimately has negative effects on people’s mindset and performance. Therefore, I believe it represents an undesirable trend in contemporary society.
